            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L27505376a62d4ec997fca1485f1e76cc" n="12353">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፋድል</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>fādǝl</quote>
                        </cit> <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="adjectivum">adj.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>great</quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>excellent</quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>superior</quote>
                        </cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለኢዮስያስኒ፡ ኢኮነት፡ ሎቱ፡ መዊእ፡ ከመ፡ መዊኦትከ። በእንተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ሠናየ፡ ገብሩ፡ ቀደምት፡ ዘአዔረዩከ፡ ምስሌሆሙ፡ እምአሐዱ፡ ኅብር፡ ወኢያእከዩ፡ ደኃሪትኒ፡ ዘረሰዩከ፡ ፋድለ፡ እምኔሆሙ፡ እምክፍል፡ ካልእ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>Therefore, the previous ones (those who made such comparisons) did well who made you equal with them for one feature (lit.: one side); and will not dishonour (you) those to come who make you superior to them in another chapter.</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosI"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 42 § 72 (ed.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosII"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 24 § 72 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንከራቲሁ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አቡነ፡ ብፁዓዊ። ፋድል</foreign> ʻ<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>the wonders of this holy father of ours, the blessed, gracious</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 112 (408) l. 11-12 (ed.); 113 (409) l. 14-15 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, (ʻThe term <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>fadǝl</quote>
                        </cit>, very common in Gǝʿǝz hagiographic texts is an Arabic loanword, faḍl, meaning “virtuous”. It is a title referred very often to Filiṗṗos (ca. 1323-1406) of Däbrä Bizän, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1901FilposYohannes"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 68</citedRange>
                        </bibl>.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 113 (409) n. 212</citedRange>
                        </bibl>. Teodros Abraha’s translation of <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>fādǝl</quote>
                        </cit> as ‘gracious’ is doubtful.) <nd/> </sense>
                </entry>
